      <hr />
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <div class="definition">
         <div>
            <p>Medium of performance term that is equivalent to the 162 medium of performance
               term of the same record. It links headings within a system or from different 
               thesauri or authority fields.
            </p>
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr />
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <div class="guidelines">
         <div>
            <p>Most of the content designators defined for field 762 are the same as those defined
               for
               field 162 (Heading-Medium of Performance Term), field 462 (See From Tracing-Medium
               of
               Performance Term), and field 562 (See Also From Tracing-Medium of Performance Term).
               Description, guidelines, and input conventions for shared content designators are
               given
               in the <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/adx62.html">X62 Medium of Performance Term-General Information</a></em> section.
            </p>
            <p>Guidelines for applying the second indicator, subfield $w (Control subfield),
            subfield $2 (Source of heading or term), subfield $i (Relationship information),
               and subfield $4 (Relationship code) in field 762 are given in the <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/authority/ad7xx.html">7XX Heading Linking Entries-General Information</a></em> section.
            </p>
         </div>
